The paper proposes a machine learning approach for learning determinantal point processes (DPPs) from labeled training data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed approach to the task of extractive summarization, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of features, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on data from the DUC 2003/04 multi-document summarization task, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for processing text.
